            What is LSRI?
          Heading link



 
Copy link








The LSRI is one of the nation’s leaders in the learning sciences, home of researchers and Ph.D students who shed light on how the learning process works and design innovative learning environments with a sharp focus on the practical impacts of their work. A leading grant-revenue generator in the College of Liberal Arts and Sciences, we are also home to UIC’s Ph.D. program in learning sciences.











            At the Top
          Heading link



 
Copy link









                                              25                                            
The College of Liberal Arts and Sciences, the largest college at UIC, consists of 25 departments, including the LSRI.








                                              3                                            
Within LAS, the LSRI's research-generated funding is among the top three.












